  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Advancing anti-corruption practices in Ghana (AAPG)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mobile phone penetration in Ghana now is well over 100% nationally. What this means is that most Ghanaians have at least one SIM card but in most cases 2 or 3. In rural areas, mobile penetration is close to 80% which means that most households have at means to a mobile phone. VOTO Mobile and GCRN want to use  a combination of mobile phones and community radio outreach to advance anti-corruption in Ghana using a two-pronged approach</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Valuable and evidence-based data on corruption instances and perceptions across the 6 regions. 

&#x2022;                Upward movement in citizens understanding and perceptions on anti-corruption mechanisms as measured through mobile phone surveys. 

&#x2022;                Improvements in development across the 6 regions as measured by the DLT 2018 and 2019. 

&#x2022;                Sustained impact through on-demand information portal</narrative>
  </description>
